{"word":"ἱππότης","slug":"ἱππότης","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἱππότης</b></el> <el>(ἱππότης, ου,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἵππος'><el>ἵππος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a driver</i> or <i>rider of horses, a horseman, knight</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>eques</el>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>as <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a>, <el>ἱππότης λεώς</el> <i>the horse, the horsemen</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}